"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0802-1463188-odonovan-mccarthy-olympics-rowing\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Ryan Clarke  Paul O'Donovan and Fintan McCarthy rowed into the history books by retaining their Olympic title in the final of the men's lightweight double sculls at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 11, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Clarke\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4669678503966577e-12, \"text\": \"Ryan Clarke\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Clarke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Clarke\"}, {\"begin\": 13, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_O'Donovan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul O'Donovan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_O'Donovan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_O'Donovan\"}, {\"begin\": 32, \"end\": 47, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fintan_McCarthy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fintan McCarthy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fintan_McCarthy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fintan_McCarthy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"O'Donovan has become the first Irish athlete to win a medal at three Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 178, \"to\": 261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 209, \"end\": 214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"score\": 0.8572664289478968, \"rank\": 0.1643650698315507, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Winning gold again \\\"was always the aim\\\", according to McCarthy, but O'Donovan claimed the historic feat was \\\"a fluke, to be honest\\\".\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 317, \"end\": 325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\", \"score\": 0.8343526472395112, \"rank\": 0.19446214573867313, \"text\": \"McCarthy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's definitely going down as a fluke in my eyes, that's about it,\\\" he told RT\\u00c9 Sport.\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 476, \"end\": 485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT\\u00c9_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9999999789533833, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9 Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT\\u00c9_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RT\\u00c9_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the duo finished in a time of 6:10.99 to seal back-to-back goldsin what was a dominant display, finishing almost three seconds clear of second-place Italy.\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 646, \"end\": 651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5981413070747824, \"rank\": 0.6717810911031132, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, McCarthy joins his crew-mate in the elite club of Irish competitors to win a medal at more than one Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 667, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\", \"score\": 0.8343526472395112, \"rank\": 0.19446214573867313, \"text\": \"McCarthy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\"}, {\"begin\": 717, \"end\": 722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"score\": 0.8572664289478968, \"rank\": 0.1643650698315507, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old is the fifth person to join the list and the second just this week after boxer Kellie Harrington also guaranteed at least a bronze in the 60kg category she won in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kellie_Harrington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kellie Harrington\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kellie_Harrington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kellie_Harrington\"}, {\"begin\": 962, \"end\": 967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9997351122019426, \"rank\": 0.0002649579555576729, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"O'Donovan (30) won the first of his three medals alongside brother Gary at Rio 2016, where they took silver.\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1078, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was then partnered with McCarthy and they went on to win gold at the Covid-19 pandemic-delayed Tokyo Games in 2021.\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1107, \"end\": 1115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\", \"score\": 0.8343526472395112, \"rank\": 0.19446214573867313, \"text\": \"McCarthy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, they became the first Irish athletes to win golds at successive Games since Pat O'Callaghan in the men's hammer throw at the 1928 and 1932 Olympics.\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1229, \"end\": 1234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"score\": 0.8572664289478968, \"rank\": 0.1643650698315507, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1283, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_O'Callaghan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pat O'Callaghan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_O'Callaghan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_O'Callaghan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Boxer Paddy Barnes rounds out the list of Irish athletes to medal at multiple Olympics.\", \"from\": 1357, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1363, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paddy_Barnes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paddy Barnes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paddy_Barnes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paddy_Barnes\"}, {\"begin\": 1399, \"end\": 1404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"score\": 0.8572664289478968, \"rank\": 0.1643650698315507, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won bronze at both the 2008 Beijing Games and the 2012 London Games.\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1517, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On both occasions he lost to Chinese boxer Zou Shiming, who twice went on to win light-flyweight (49kg) gold after defeating Barnes.\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1548, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.8603669863161982, \"rank\": 0.15684476370095393, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1566, \"end\": 1573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shiming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shiming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shiming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shiming\"}, {\"begin\": 1644, \"end\": 1650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barnes_Rugby_Football_Club\", \"score\": 0.981665384914076, \"rank\": 0.010896482487936524, \"text\": \"Barnes\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barnes_Rugby_Football_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barnes_Rugby_Football_Club\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland could also set a fresh record in terms of overall medal tallies at the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1653, \"end\": 1660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998747513653696, \"rank\": 0.00012497072423352443, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the exploits of McCarthy and O'Donovan, Harrington, Philip Doyle and Daire Lynch (rowing bronze) and Daniel Wiffen (800m swimming gold), Ireland are already up to five medals and currently 13th in the overall 2024 table.\", \"from\": 1746, \"to\": 1976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1772, \"end\": 1780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\", \"score\": 0.8343526472395112, \"rank\": 0.19446214573867313, \"text\": \"McCarthy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\"}, {\"begin\": 1808, \"end\": 1820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Doyle_(American_football)\", \"score\": 0.809412548681283, \"rank\": 0.22437673130189478, \"text\": \"Philip Doyle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Doyle_(American_football)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Doyle_(American_football)\"}, {\"begin\": 1893, \"end\": 1900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998747513653696, \"rank\": 0.00012497072423352443, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"London 2012 was Ireland's most successful Games with five medals but that only included one gold - for Katie Taylor - so another podium finish would make 2024 the most glorious year.\", \"from\": 1978, \"to\": 2160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1978, \"end\": 1989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6629251292210856e-15, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1994, \"end\": 2001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998747513653696, \"rank\": 0.00012497072423352443, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the likes of Wiffen, who goes again in the 1500m freestyle, pommel horse world champion Rhys McClenaghan and our European champion athletes still to come in Paris, six medals or more is looking like an extremely achievable goal.\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2255, \"end\": 2271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rhys McClenaghan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\"}, {\"begin\": 2324, \"end\": 2329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999900505827, \"rank\": 9.949418474698272e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow theRT\\u00c9 Sport WhatsApp channelfor the best news, interviews, analysis and features, as well as details of our sports coverage across all RT\\u00c9 platforms.\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2540, \"end\": 2543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9835396432123026, \"rank\": 0.013767790549921992, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2595, \"end\": 2618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851268295, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 2620, \"end